, is revealed to have been a tireless and energetic promoter of Beethoven’s music in the later nineteenth century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMusicy18th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aMusicy19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2021. 7aMUSIC / Genres & Styles / Classical.2bisacsh  aBeethoven.  aBonn.  aCharles Hallé.  aChristian Gottlob Neefe.  aConcerto No. 4 in G major.  aErste Liebe.  aGeorge Thomson.  aJohann Michael Sailer.  aNeefe.  aString Quintet Op. 104.  achamber music.  aexpression marks.  alate style.  ametronome.  avariations.  awind music.1 aCooper, Barry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCooper, Barry, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCooper, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDerry, Siân, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEckerson, Sara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarlow, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNoorduin, Marten, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPereira, Artur, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPilcher, Matthew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPilcher, Matthew, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWorsley, Kris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 avan der Zanden, Jos, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152615569640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526155696423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526155696/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles